const cleaningPackages = [ { name: 'Basic Cleaning', services: ['Debris removal', 'Surface cleaning', 'Basic plant trimming'], price: '$125', duration: '2-3 hours', image: '/images/IMG_2770.jpg' }, { name: 'Standard Cleaning', services: ['Debris removal', 'Algae control', 'Filter cleaning', 'Plant maintenance'], price: '$195', duration: '4-5 hours', image: '/images/IMG_2775.jpg' }, { name: 'Deep Cleaning', services: ['All standard services', 'Sediment removal', 'Water change', 'Equipment inspection'], price: '$295', duration: '6-8 hours', image: '/images/IMG_2779.jpg' } ]; return (

Our Cleaning Process

{/* Seasonal Cleaning */}

Seasonal Cleaning Schedule

Different seasons require different cleaning approaches

Spring Cleaning

Remove winter debris and prepare for the growing season

  • Remove fallen leaves and debris
  • Clean filters and equipment
  • Test water quality
  • Plant new aquatic plants
Schedule Spring Cleaning

Summer Maintenance

Maintain water quality during peak growing season

  • Control algae growth
  • Clean filters regularly
  • Monitor water levels
  • Trim overgrown plants
Schedule Summer Maintenance

Fall Preparation

Prepare pond for winter and prevent spring problems

  • Remove dying plants
  • Clean filters thoroughly
  • Remove excess debris
  • Prepare for winter
